<br>

<b><u> 2-DAY OPTION: WEEKDAY or WEEKEND CLASSES </u></b><br>
Thursday &amp; Friday, <b>March 2nd &amp; 3rd</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Saturday &amp; Sunday, <b>March 4th &amp; 5th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Thursday &amp; Friday, <b>March 9th &amp; 10th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Saturday &amp; Sunday, <b>March 11th &amp; 12th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Thursday &amp; Friday, <b>March 16th &amp; 17th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Saturday &amp; Sunday, <b>March 18th &amp; 19th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Thursday &amp; Friday, <b>March 23rd &amp; 24th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Saturday &amp; Sunday, <b>March 25th &amp; 26th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Thursday &amp; Friday, <b>March 30th &amp; 31st</b>, 8:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><u>ARMED SECURITY REQUALIFICATION COURSE -- 1 DAY, 4-HOUR COURSE</u></b>
<br>
The cost of the session is $65.00 plus ammunition and range fee of an additional $75.00. Range and written test required by state.<br>
Wednesday, <b>March 1st</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Friday, <b>March 3rd</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Sunday,<b> March 5th</b>, 10:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Friday, <b>March 10th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Sunday,<b> March 12th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Wednesday, <b>March 15th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM <br>
Friday, <b>March 17th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Sunday,<b> March 19th</b>, 10:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Friday, <b>March 24th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Sunday,<b> March 26th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
Wednesday, <b>March 29th</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM <br>
Friday, <b>March 31st</b>, 8:00 AM -- 4:00 PM<br>
<br>
</p>
<hr>
<p>
<h2><b><u> 8-HOUR HANDCUFFING &amp; BATON Training to Certification</u></b></h2>
<br>

This is an 8-hour certification course sanctioned by Armament Systems and Procedures, Inc. (ASP). You will learn the basic techniques used by officers from an ASP certified trainer. Four (4) hours will be spent on handcuffing and four (4) hours on expandable baton. After completion of the class, you will be certified on both tools. Students will receive a nationally accredited certificate for the course they complete as well as an ASP Certification Card. If you have a baton and/or cuffs, please bring the items to class; if not it will be supplied. Please wear comfortable clothes.  <br>
The cost of each class is $100; $200 for both.<br>
<br>
Saturday, <b>March 18th</b>, 10:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
Saturday, <b>April 15th</b>, 10:00 AM -- 6:00 PM<br>
<br>
</p>
<hr>
<p>
<h2><b><u>Private Detective Course</u></b></h2>
<br>

Learn what you need to become a licensed Private Investigator. Students will be taught about firearm training, security, detective work, as well as skip tracing, databases, pretext calls, court records, equipment, surveillance, and more. <br>
<u>The cost of each class is $125, pre-registration and pre-payment are required.</u><br>
<br>

Wednesday, <b>March 22nd</b>, 6:00 PM -- 10:00 PM<br>
Wednesday, <b>April 19th</b>, 6:00 PM -- 10:00 PM<br>

<br>
</p>
<hr>
<p>

<h2><b><u>Other Services Offered</u></b></h2><br>

<b><u>Private Shooting Lessons</b></u><br>
3-hours classroom instruction, 3-hours instruction at the range. $300 per individual. For groups of 10 or more, $200 per student.  This does not include the $75 range fee per person.  By appointment only.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Gun Safety / S.I.R.T. LASER</b></u><br>
We use the S.I.R.T. LASER Pistol in the classroom. This model handgun shoots a laser beam that shows where the student would have hit the target if they were using real ammunition. This state-of-the-art technology lets the instructor and student see exactly what they are doing right, and where correction is needed in the shooting fundamentals BEFORE using live ammunition. <br>
<br>
<b><u>FOID, ICC or PERC Card Application Assistance</b></u><br>
We are offering services for anyone who needs assistance filling out their FOID, Illinois Concealed Carry, or PERC card application. This service is also available to FOID renewal, and address changes.  FOID, ICC or PERC card assistance are $30.00 each. Address changes are $20.00.<br><br>

<b>DISCLAIMER:</b> We are only charging you the service fee. <b>It is your responsibility to pay for your application fee -- a debit or credit card is required for payment to the state.</b> Note that the online application on the ISP website will have a Criminal Background History part that can affect your eligibility for a FOID card and/or Concealed Carry Permit. If you are applying for your ICC, please be prepared to provide 10 years of residential history (addresses AND the dates that you lived at each location).  If you have further questions or to schedule an appointment, call us at 773-355-1691.
<br>
<br>
<b><u>PERC License Print Out and Lamination</b></u><br>
The <i>Illinois Department of Financial and Professional Regulation</i> (IDFPR) no longer sends out paper licenses for PERC cards.  PERC and other licenses under IDFPR may be accessed and printed through their eLicense website.  Printed/laminated cards are $15.00.
<br>
<br>
<b><u>Wall Certificates</b></u><br>
If you'd like a wall certificate with our license number and seal for any of our classes it is $25.00<br><br>
<b><u>Lost Certificates</b></u><br>
Per the contract you signed when taking any of our classes, we charge a fee of $55.00 for lost certificates. You must provide your full name, which class you took, and the date(s) you took the class. It will take between 7-14 business days to retrieve your file from our storage unit. You may stop by the office, send us an email, or call us at 773-355-1691. NOTE: the $55.00 fee must be paid up front.<br>
<br>

<p>
WE HELP YOU OBTAIN ALL NECESSARY CREDENTIALS REQUIRED BY THE STATE: PERC APPLICATION, FOID, FINGERPRINTING! FINGERPRINTING IS DONE ON SITE. PRIOR REGISTRATION IS NOT REQUIRED -- BUT RECOMMENDED FOR ALL SECURITY CLASSES. <br>
THERE IS AN ADDITIONAL FEE FOR FINGERPRINTING OF $60.00 AND A $55.00 LICENSE FEE. BOTH ARE REQUIRED BY THE STATE OF ILLINOIS WHEN APPLYING FOR A PERC CARD. <br>
<br>
ATTENTION: PLEASE ENSURE THAT THE FACULTY CONDUCTING YOUR TRAINING IS A STATE CERTIFIED FACILITY AND THEY HAVE THEIR OWN STATE FIREARM LICENSE TRAINING NUMBER. BEING A SECURITY AGENCY AND HAVING A SECURITY AGENCY LICENSE DOESN'T MEAN YOU ARE A STATE RECOGNIZED SECURITY TRAINING SCHOOL. <br>
<br>
<b>ALL CLASSES ARE SUBJECT TO PRICE CHANGE AND/OR CANCELLATION WITHOUT NOTICE<br>
NO REFUNDS -- CREDIT FOR FUTURE CLASSES ONLY<br></b>
<br>
CASH OR MONEY ORDER MADE PAYABLE TO CHICAGOLAND DETECTIVE SERVICES<br>
You must also sign the No-Refund form if you are pre-paying for a class. See the form on our website or when you walk-in the office.
